The paper presents a new approach for instance segmentation in biological images using a fully-convolutional network and clustering in the embeddings space. This work involves computer vision (CV) techniques such as clustering and convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which are commonly found in the cs.CV sub-category. Additionally, the use of embeddings and regression loss suggests a focus on machine learning (ML) and deep learning (DL), which are also present in the cs.LG and cs.AI sub-categories. The use of sine waves and frequencies may also suggest a focus on signal processing, which is present in the cs.NE sub-category. Finally, the use of clustering and embeddings for segmentation may also suggest a focus on information retrieval (IR), which is present in the cs.IR sub-category.
